        "title": "fix(replay): rewrite response ids during replay",
        "body": "Follow-up for openclaw/mcporter#175.\n\nThis keeps the record/replay feature direction from PR #175 but addresses the actionable review blockers that were preventing merge:\n\n- rewrites replayed JSON-RPC response ids to the active request id, so clients waiting on the current id do not hang\n- updates the regression test to prove replay returns id `99` when the active request id is `99`, even if the recording used id `1`\n- changes the README wording from \"shareable repros\" to \"redacted repros\"\n- adds explicit redaction guidance for raw NDJSON recordings in `docs/record-replay.md`\n\nVerification:\n\n- `pnpm exec vitest run tests/record-replay.test.ts`\n- `pnpm check`\n- `pnpm test`\n\nNote: the first full `pnpm test` run inside Codex sandbox failed on local `listen EPERM` for loopback and Unix sockets. The same command passed host-side.\n",
